        <h3>Improving site performance</h3>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail"><a href="#ControllareIndiciPrestazione"> Checking performance indicators</a>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail"><a href="#IntervernireSuDispositiviUnita"> Device and unit actions</a>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <hr style="color: #808080;height: 1px;float: alignleft;" color="#808080" size="0" align="center" width="100%" />
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="AprireSessioneinternet"></a> Checking PlantVisorPRO Locale via Internet</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Connect to the site via Internet
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Connect to the Internet and open Internet Explorer</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>In the address bar, enter the static IP assigned to PlantVisorPRO Embedded (see chapter <a href="PVPRO_loc__modalita_di_connessione.htm">Connection modes</a>): the logon page opens</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>Open PlantVisorPRO Locale as if it were on site</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="PVPRO_loc__modalita_di_connessione.htm">PVPRO loc: connection modes</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="RisalireCauseDelGuasto"></a> Tracing fault causes from the received notification</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check global alarms
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Notification text should be sufficiently descriptive to indicate faults.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Alarms</span>,  <span style="font-weight: bold;">Active alarms</span> page, use the notification time to check which alarms were triggered first (see chapter  <a href="Allarmi__allarmi_attivi.htm">Active alarms</a>) </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>Double-click an alarm to open details and check if for actions by the site user (see chapter <a href="Allarmi__dettaglio_allarme.htm">Alarm details</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="4">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Alarms</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Reset alarms</span> page, double click to open cleared alarm details (see chapter <a href="Allarmi__allarmi_rientrati.htm">Cleared alarms</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Force minor alarms clear
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Alarms</span><span>, double-click a minor alarm and force it clear  </span>(see chapter <a href="Allarmi__dettaglio_allarme.htm">Alarm details</a></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check global events
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Events</span> check the event sequence, starting from the most recent event (probably near the date-time of the first alarm) to the event that caused the alarm (see chapter <a href="Eventi__introduzione.htm">Events</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="4">
                <p class="ActionDetail">If necessary, run a targeted search
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Search</span><a href="Ricerca__allarmi.htm">, </a>find and print alarms and events that meet search criteria (see chapter <a href="Ricerca__eventi.htm">Alarm search</a> and Event search).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="5">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Analyze the behavior of devices in alarm conditions.
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Click <img src="../Resources/Images/AllarmiLink.png" style="border: none;width: 20px;height: 20px;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="20" height="20" border="0" /> on the alarm row to open the detail page on the device in alarm conditions.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Allarmi_e_eventi__concetti_di_base.htm">Alarms and events: basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="TacitareSegnalazioni"></a> Muting any warnings</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Stop supervisor actions
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Alarms</span><span>, double-click an alarm to open details and stop any scheduled </span> supervisor actions (see chapter <a href="Allarmi__dettaglio_allarme.htm">Alarm details</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">(optional) Disabling a device</p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Site configuration</span>, double-click a line, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Edit line</span><span>,</span> disable those devices that should not trigger alarms (except the off line one) (see chapter <a href="Config-sito__dettaglio_linea.htm">Line details</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">(optional) Disable all alarm and event activities from a device</p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Site configuration</span>, double-click the line, double-click the device, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Main</span><span> page  </span>to disable the alarm and event activities (see chapter <a href="Config-dispositivo__principale.htm">Device setup: main page</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="4">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Stop auxiliary relays.
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>If necessary, in <span style="font-weight: bold;">Relay management,</span> stop relays excited by supervisor actions, tied to alarm status (see chapter <a href="Rele__introduzione.htm">Deactivating relays</a>).</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Attivita__concetti_di_base.htm">Activities basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="AnalizzareStatoDispositiviUnita"></a> Analyzing device and unit status</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Analyze the certain device group variable trends                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">SITE Global</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;groupName&gt;</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Log graph</span>: display the variables for the concerned devices and check the trend in the period concerned by the event that generated the alarm (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__grafico_HACCP_e_storico.htm">Monitoring: HACCP and log graphs</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Compare different device variable trends                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global</span><a href="Monitoraggio__grafico_HACCP_e_storico.htm">, </a>Log graph: display the variables for the concerned devices and check the trend in the period concerned by the event that generated the alarm (see chapter Monitoring: HACCP and log graphs)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Grafici__concetti_di_base.htm">Graphs basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="IntervernireSuDispositiviUnita"></a> Device and unit actions</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Checking device status and controlling the unit                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global</span>, double-click a device, Main page to:</p>
                        </li>
                        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                            <li class="p" value="1">
                                <p>check device status, </p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="2">
                                <p>check probe values,</p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="3">
                                <p>set main parameters,</p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="4">
                                <p>control the device (i.e.: clear alarms)</p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="p" value="5">
                                <p>control the unit (i.e.: turn on/off)</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>(see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio-dispositivo__pagina_principale.htm">Monitoring-device: main page</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Editing device parameters (i.e.: setpoint).
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT,<span style="font-weight: bold;"> Global</span></span> double-click a device, <a href="Monitoraggio-dispositivo__parametri.htm">Parameters page</a> to set all parameters (see chapter Monitoring- device: parameters)</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>If necessary, propagate the same settings on the same parameters for all similar devices</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Editing device group parameters (i.e.: setpoint)
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">PLANT, Global</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;groupName&gt;</span>,  <span style="font-weight: bold;">Parameters</span> page, set a value on several parameters simultaneously (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__parametri.htm">Monitoring: parameters</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>For further information, see chapter <a href="Dispositivo__concetti_di_base.htm">Devices: basic concepts</a></p>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="ControllareIndiciPrestazione"></a> Checking performance indicators</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Check how long values are out of range
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">ENERGY</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">Performance indicators (KPI) </span>, click the button for the variables to be checked to request a report and check indicators (see chapter <a href="Indicatori_di_performance__introduzione.htm">Maps: performance indicators</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /><a name="AggiugereNuoviDispositivi"></a> Adding new devices</p>
        <ol style="list-style: decimal;list-style-type: decimal;">
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="1">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Stop the engine
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p style="color: #000000;">In <span style="font-weight: bold;">System pages</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">System</span>, stop the engine</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="2">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Add the device to the line
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>In <span style="font-weight: bold;">Site setup</span>, select the line, click <img src="../Resources/Images/actions/Edit_button.png" style="border: none;float: none;width: 24px;height: 24px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="24" height="24" border="0" />, select the device type, assign an address, edit the device description and click<img src="../Resources/Images/dbllistbox/arrowdx_on.png" style="border: none;width: 54px;height: 19px;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="54" height="19" border="0" /></p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>See chapter <a href="Config-sito__dettaglio_linea.htm">Line details.</a></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="3">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Setting up a device
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>If necessary, customize the device setup by clicking <img src="../Resources/Images/actions/maintenance_on_black.png" style="border: none;border-style: none;width: 24px;height: 24px;float: none;" width="24" height="24" border="0" />: <span style="font-weight: bold;">Device setup</span> pages open.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>See chapter <a href="Config-dispositivo__introduzione.htm">Device setup</a>.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="4">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Connect the device
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="kadov-p" value="1">Physically connect the device to the serial line</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="5">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Restart the engine
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p style="color: #000000;">In <span style="font-weight: bold;">System pages</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">System</span>, restart the engine</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li class="p-ActionDetail" value="6">
                <p class="ActionDetail">Test field communications
                                                                                                </p>
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>After restarting the engine, the new device appears in  <span style="font-weight: bold;">Global</span> (see chapter <a href="Monitoraggio__pagina_principale.htm">Monitoring: main page</a>)</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
